signatures.note:
- Quire marks are written in the upper margin of the following two leaves:
18r: ፫ (once);
26r: ፬ (once).

handNote.seg:
Nomina sacra; 
three or five lines in the incipit page of each text, alternating with black lines (in one or both columns); sometimes the first line of the account proper;
Ethiopic numerals (e.g., fol. 26va, l.15) or their elements;
elements of the punctuation signs and of the crux ansata.
